After SARS-CoV-2 S-protein RBD domain docked with ACE2 via ZDOCK, 8 receptor-ligand complex models were obtained. Energy optimization and model screening were carried out for all conformations using PDBePISA database, and the specific data are shown in Table 5
. The best model is the one with the largest surface area, the smallest surface energy and the most hydrogen bonds (Xu et al., xxxx). After comprehensive consideration, complex2 was selected as the near-natural model (Fig 5-B). Analysis of the key binding sites of SARS-CoV-2 and ACE2 showed that SARS-CoV-2 S-protein Arg426 and Tyr436, respectively, combined with Gln325/Glu329 and Asp38/Gln42 of ACE2 through hydrogen bonds and formed an interaction interface with adjacent residues (Fig 6
), which is consistent with previous research results of Hao Pei team (Zefeng, 2020).
